WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.650 --> 00:00:06.740
Dear young people, it is a real pleasure
and a blessing to see you here in such

00:00:06.740 --> 00:00:10.633
large numbers; it reminds me a little
of this Gospel, this crowd gathered

00:00:10.633 --> 00:00:14.525
around Jesus, for they pressed on
Him so that they might touch Him.

00:00:14.525 --> 00:00:19.017
We are still in this ongoing cycle of
talks about love, this theme we keep

00:00:19.017 --> 00:00:20.814
returning to again with hopeful hearts.

00:00:20.814 --> 00:00:24.107
Many times I hear from you,
dear young people, that when

00:00:24.107 --> 00:00:27.701
the topic is love you ask a wide
variety of thoughtful questions.

00:00:27.701 --> 00:00:31.893
One of the deepest questions that today’s
young people carry is not what you

00:00:31.893 --> 00:00:33.690
think; which particular question is that?

00:00:35.570 --> 00:00:39.692
It's not about whom I will love,
in any possible future, not about

00:00:39.692 --> 00:00:41.278
any particular person at all.

00:00:41.278 --> 00:00:45.400
Unfortunately, that's not it at all,
and the matter goes deeper than that.

00:00:45.400 --> 00:00:49.522
But the question is whether I am
even worthy of someone loving me,

00:00:49.522 --> 00:00:51.425
a question that haunts many people.

00:00:51.425 --> 00:00:55.548
It would seem only natural for us
to ask ourselves the question of

00:00:55.548 --> 00:00:59.987
whom I will love, and for you to ask
yourselves that same question too.

00:00:59.987 --> 00:01:04.744
However, in talking with you, I can
plainly see that for some people the very

00:01:04.744 --> 00:01:08.549
foundations of their sense of self, of
their identity, have become unsettled.

00:01:08.549 --> 00:01:12.672
So, instead of asking yourself who
I will love, a great many young

00:01:12.672 --> 00:01:16.794
people have reached a point where
they say to themselves, "am I even

00:01:16.794 --> 00:01:18.380
worthy that someone loves me?"

00:01:18.380 --> 00:01:22.757
What has happened to you that you
have lost that deep, core sense of

00:01:22.757 --> 00:01:26.510
your own identity and the genuine,
lasting value of the person you

00:01:26.510 --> 00:01:28.699
are, in the life you lead today?

00:01:28.699 --> 00:01:33.702
If we pose such a question and live in
a time when your worth is constantly

00:01:33.702 --> 00:01:37.142
defined by a dizzying variety of likes,
comments, successes, and competitions,

00:01:37.142 --> 00:01:41.207
and that is precisely what social
media keeps feeding you, day after day.

00:01:41.207 --> 00:01:44.960
And because of that, many young people
lose their identity and consequently

00:01:44.960 --> 00:01:49.025
self-worth, and they ask themselves these
kinds of questions: Am I really worth

00:01:49.025 --> 00:01:54.341
anything at all, or do I count for nothing
in this world, in this life we share.

00:01:54.341 --> 00:01:58.093
That is why many young people
struggle to see their worth clearly

00:01:58.093 --> 00:01:59.970
and to know where they belong.

00:01:59.970 --> 00:02:01.854
Will anyone actually love me anymore?

00:02:01.854 --> 00:02:03.425
And why is that so?

00:02:03.425 --> 00:02:07.194
Because in this world you follow,
in which you live, especially this

00:02:07.194 --> 00:02:10.335
online world of social media, it
teaches entirely different values.

00:02:10.335 --> 00:02:10.649
How?

00:02:10.649 --> 00:02:13.790
For example, if you are
seen, it means you exist.

00:02:13.790 --> 00:02:16.931
If someone chooses you, it
means you are worth something.

00:02:16.931 --> 00:02:20.386
If you are alone, the question
arises: what's wrong with you?

00:02:20.386 --> 00:02:24.783
That is why people wonder whether anyone
will love them when they feel unseen.

00:02:24.783 --> 00:02:28.238
We live inside this online
world where value seems tied to

00:02:28.238 --> 00:02:29.495
visibility and prompt responses.

00:02:29.495 --> 00:02:33.264
And yet the question remains:
what is wrong with you if you

00:02:33.264 --> 00:02:34.834
are not noticed by others?

00:02:35.984 --> 00:02:40.197
I believe the hardest question
for you all is how to get

00:02:40.197 --> 00:02:42.303
married, how to become a wife.

00:02:42.303 --> 00:02:45.462
Or why you are alone, why you are single.

00:02:45.462 --> 00:02:48.621
Because the foundations of
our values have been shaken.

00:02:48.621 --> 00:02:52.834
That means I only truly exist
if I am seen and noticed.

00:02:52.834 --> 00:02:59.152
Only when someone chooses me, or sends for
me, or invites me in some way, do I become

00:02:59.152 --> 00:03:03.715
worth anything, at least in quotation
marks, but that is not the point.

00:03:03.715 --> 00:03:05.119
That is not Christianity.

00:03:05.519 --> 00:03:09.856
Because, at the end of the day, if we
examine things from that perspective, in

00:03:09.856 --> 00:03:14.193
the final analysis, you are worth exactly
as much as you are desired by others.

00:03:14.193 --> 00:03:18.819
Are you all equally desirable, and are you
not all at the same ages, nor desirable

00:03:18.819 --> 00:03:20.842
in the same way, really and truly?

00:03:20.842 --> 00:03:24.601
Does all this, in fact, mean that
you are, at this point, truly

00:03:24.601 --> 00:03:26.336
no longer worth anything at all?

00:03:26.336 --> 00:03:29.516
Well, you're not, but alas,
the expiry date does not apply

00:03:29.516 --> 00:03:31.251
to you as a person, indeed.

00:03:31.251 --> 00:03:35.009
So why, then, have some people, who
once valued them, accepted that for

00:03:35.009 --> 00:03:39.346
them a love story has reached its
end, and that their value is no longer

00:03:39.346 --> 00:03:41.370
held in esteem by anyone at all?

00:03:42.195 --> 00:03:44.631
Where, in all honesty, have we gone wrong?

00:03:44.631 --> 00:03:49.199
That statement says that if you are
not in a relationship, if no one truly

00:03:49.199 --> 00:03:54.071
wants you, if no one ever chooses you,
if no one ever selects you, then surely

00:03:54.071 --> 00:03:56.203
you are not worth anything at all.

00:03:56.203 --> 00:03:57.726
That, however, is not true.

00:03:57.726 --> 00:03:58.640
Why is that?

00:03:58.640 --> 00:04:01.989
Because we need to view this,
in a biblically informed way.

00:04:01.989 --> 00:04:06.557
We must not, in any way, measure our
lives and our worth, our very identity,

00:04:06.557 --> 00:04:10.821
by the changes and fashions of social
media that now seem to govern our

00:04:10.821 --> 00:04:15.085
modern society, but rather by the
timeless truth of what God says to us.

00:04:15.605 --> 00:04:19.634
Do you remember that not so
long ago we publicly celebrated

00:04:19.634 --> 00:04:20.732
Jesus’ baptism together?

00:04:20.732 --> 00:04:25.860
When Jesus was baptised, a voice was
heard saying, “This is my beloved Son,”

00:04:25.860 --> 00:04:31.355
and those present were filled with
awe. God did not wait for Jesus to do

00:04:31.355 --> 00:04:36.849
anything at all in order to declare
him as His beloved Son. Nor did God

00:04:36.849 --> 00:04:42.343
put to him the question, “Will you
be my beloved Son if you should ever

00:04:42.343 --> 00:04:47.105
succeed?” You will indeed be my beloved
Son provided that people accept you.

00:04:47.105 --> 00:04:50.041
You will be my beloved
Son if you should succeed.

00:04:50.041 --> 00:04:52.097
See, God does not work that way.

00:04:52.097 --> 00:04:55.327
God tells him who He is
before he has done anything.

00:04:55.327 --> 00:04:59.733
For we know that this marks the beginning
of his public ministry, the work of

00:04:59.733 --> 00:05:02.082
God beginning to be made clear in him.

00:05:02.082 --> 00:05:04.138
And God loves him
sincerely, without pretense.

00:05:04.138 --> 00:05:07.368
Nor because of success, nor because
others notice him, nor because

00:05:07.368 --> 00:05:10.892
others accept him—these are not the
foundations of how He regards him.

00:05:10.892 --> 00:05:14.417
Therefore, dear young people, you are
not valued only if someone notices

00:05:14.417 --> 00:05:18.528
you, if someone seeks you, if someone
praises you, if you are successful; your

00:05:18.528 --> 00:05:22.640
worth does not depend on applause or
recognition, but on being known by God.

00:05:22.780 --> 00:05:26.358
You're not, because, in that
case, it would not possess a

00:05:26.358 --> 00:05:27.660
genuinely authentic identity today.

00:05:27.660 --> 00:05:32.215
Your identity and ours do not come from
success; value comes first and foremost,

00:05:32.215 --> 00:05:34.492
precisely because of merit, in life today.

00:05:34.492 --> 00:05:38.071
The problem I carry inside me
is that, sadly, most people

00:05:38.071 --> 00:05:39.698
today live by backward values.

00:05:39.698 --> 00:05:43.602
If someone loves me, it means
I am truly valuable, and it

00:05:43.602 --> 00:05:44.903
gives my life significance.

00:05:44.903 --> 00:05:50.759
If I am in a relationship, then I matter
quite a lot to others as well in life.

00:05:50.759 --> 00:05:54.013
If someone chooses me, then
I have some intrinsic value

00:05:54.013 --> 00:05:55.640
that guides my decisions now.

00:05:56.700 --> 00:06:00.414
Believe me, a great many young
people think about their own worth

00:06:00.414 --> 00:06:02.581
in this exact way, in life today.

00:06:02.581 --> 00:06:07.844
And what will we do if we hold this
inverted view of values, this odd way of

00:06:07.844 --> 00:06:10.011
thinking about what truly matters in life?

00:06:10.011 --> 00:06:13.416
What will we do when a
relationship breaks up in life?

00:06:13.416 --> 00:06:16.821
What will we do when a
marriage falls apart in life?

00:06:16.821 --> 00:06:20.845
I meet daily those who were, who
had, such sturdy foundations in life.

00:06:20.845 --> 00:06:24.870
And when a relationship or a marriage
breaks, it is not the relationship

00:06:24.870 --> 00:06:28.585
that shatters, but the identity itself
that cracks and crumbles within life.

00:06:29.555 --> 00:06:32.951
A person's value shatters within
them, leaving a hollow place inside,

00:06:32.951 --> 00:06:35.112
a gap that changes how they live.

00:06:35.112 --> 00:06:39.125
And a person does not merely stay
because of the beloved, but carries

00:06:39.125 --> 00:06:43.139
on even without a fragment of who
they are, losing sight of themselves.

00:06:43.139 --> 00:06:47.461
Because their own sense of self, their
own value, was steered by another person.

00:06:47.461 --> 00:06:52.401
Or by the fact that they were loved, or
longed for, or simply noticed by others.

00:06:52.401 --> 00:06:56.415
And I see today now that many
people experience it in this way.

00:06:56.415 --> 00:07:00.120
But why am I saying this, you
might ask, in first place?

00:07:00.120 --> 00:07:04.144
God operates by a logic that is
fundamentally different from human logic.

00:07:04.144 --> 00:07:07.163
God simply and unconditionally
loves us, all of us.

00:07:07.163 --> 00:07:11.188
He loves us exactly as we are,
without any conditions at all.

00:07:11.188 --> 00:07:15.884
Believe me, many young people seek
happiness; of course it is nice to be

00:07:15.884 --> 00:07:20.244
in love and to discover and realise
who you are through that experience.

00:07:20.244 --> 00:07:24.605
But another person can never replace
God, nor can they replace your deep

00:07:24.605 --> 00:07:27.288
dignity that you are a child of God.

00:07:27.288 --> 00:07:30.307
There is no sunshine in
love, nor any compensation.

00:07:30.307 --> 00:07:35.673
Many people do that, and that is why
I said it, because they do not truly

00:07:35.673 --> 00:07:39.027
know themselves, their identity,
or their weaknesses, and then when

00:07:39.027 --> 00:07:43.052
something like that happens not only
does love or a relationship fail,

00:07:43.052 --> 00:07:44.729
but the entire system collapses.

00:07:46.039 --> 00:07:51.037
Therefore Jesus listens to the words
spoken by God, and you are my beloved Son.

00:07:51.037 --> 00:07:56.367
This is what I want to tell you above
all, so that you, young people, may

00:07:56.367 --> 00:08:01.698
be able to love well, may be able
to marry, and may be able to build

00:08:01.698 --> 00:08:03.030
one good, lasting relationship.

00:08:03.030 --> 00:08:07.695
First you must become aware of your
identity, and you must be emotionally and

00:08:07.695 --> 00:08:12.026
spiritually healed and restored, sound
and upright, so that you will not become

00:08:12.026 --> 00:08:14.025
emotionally vampiric to the other person.

00:08:14.025 --> 00:08:16.023
And this is added too often.

00:08:16.023 --> 00:08:20.687
Many people, when they lose someone or
a relationship, you know how many people

00:08:20.687 --> 00:08:25.018
reach out to me every day: yesterday
my relationship ended or I’m breaking

00:08:25.018 --> 00:08:27.017
up or something—what should I do?

00:08:27.017 --> 00:08:29.682
If your relationship hadn't
broken yesterday, you wouldn't

00:08:29.682 --> 00:08:31.347
even think of God today.

00:08:31.347 --> 00:08:35.012
Come on, have a go: those in
relationships, those in marriages.

00:08:35.012 --> 00:08:39.010
Try it: would your life function
if there were no people around?

00:08:39.010 --> 00:08:41.918
How would you actually
feel, I wonder, honestly?

00:08:41.918 --> 00:08:44.827
Would you perhaps, even,
be able to survive?

00:08:44.827 --> 00:08:48.827
Or is that really the end
of your world right now?

00:08:48.827 --> 00:08:53.190
It’s over; we have nothing left, and
everything has fallen completely apart.

00:08:53.190 --> 00:08:57.917
And that, then, makes it very
clear to us what we have actually

00:08:57.917 --> 00:09:00.098
put first in our lives, really.

00:09:00.098 --> 00:09:04.461
And when we enter relationships as
immature, truly unaware of our own

00:09:04.461 --> 00:09:06.643
identity, what happens to many people?

00:09:06.643 --> 00:09:08.824
A relationship becomes,
unfortunately, an addiction.

00:09:09.245 --> 00:09:12.784
Every relationship, if it has ever been
healthy, should allow absolute freedom

00:09:12.784 --> 00:09:14.553
and trust between the people involved.

00:09:14.553 --> 00:09:18.387
If you are so utterly dependent
on that person that you no longer

00:09:18.387 --> 00:09:22.221
recognise your own identity, or even
know where you would be without that

00:09:22.221 --> 00:09:26.055
person, Burac, set aside the question
of what exactly is wrong with you.

00:09:26.055 --> 00:09:27.530
What is your identity then?

00:09:27.530 --> 00:09:31.659
If you are in a relationship that makes
you dependent upon that one person,

00:09:31.659 --> 00:09:35.788
have you perhaps turned your partner
into an idol, or into a golden calf,

00:09:35.788 --> 00:09:39.917
or into some other god, so that you
cannot function unless that person is

00:09:39.917 --> 00:09:41.982
present and actively part of your life?

00:09:41.982 --> 00:09:46.405
You know, there are people who cannot
bear to be apart for two days, whether

00:09:46.405 --> 00:09:50.240
on holiday or for work, because there
is immediately some fear that arises.

00:09:50.500 --> 00:09:54.733
Thus there can be no real,
genuine love between us if we find

00:09:54.733 --> 00:09:58.316
ourselves trapped in a state of
mutual dependence on one another.

00:09:58.316 --> 00:10:00.270
That, quite plainly, is not freedom.

00:10:00.270 --> 00:10:04.178
Secondly, what kind of love is
it when fear exists, fear of

00:10:04.178 --> 00:10:07.435
losing that person, fear that
you cannot function without them?

00:10:07.435 --> 00:10:10.692
And that is exactly what I
meant; everything about it

00:10:10.692 --> 00:10:11.995
seems inverted or reversed.

00:10:11.995 --> 00:10:16.555
And what's more, when you are emotionally
immature, when you are not aware of

00:10:16.555 --> 00:10:20.463
your own identity, the other partner
becomes the judge of your worth.

00:10:20.463 --> 00:10:24.371
In other words, love should be a
choice made freely, a conscious

00:10:24.371 --> 00:10:28.280
agreement entered into by people,
not a prison built from fear itself.

00:10:32.255 --> 00:10:33.071
That isn’t good.

00:10:33.071 --> 00:10:36.065
It’s very important you understand you’re
valuable, even without any relationship.

00:10:36.065 --> 00:10:39.332
It’s not only if you’re sought
after; it’s not only if you’re

00:10:39.332 --> 00:10:42.598
noticed; it’s not only if you’re in
a relationship that you’re worth.

00:10:42.598 --> 00:10:46.681
Many people need to hear this, and I’ll
explain why some feel, at thirty or

00:10:46.681 --> 00:10:50.491
twenty-five years old, that they are
not worth much anymore, in a world that

00:10:50.491 --> 00:10:53.486
constantly pressures people to prove
their worth and chase superficial success.

00:10:53.486 --> 00:10:57.568
I get goosebumps when I hear from young
people saying that their time has passed,

00:10:57.568 --> 00:11:01.923
and I want to help them recognise their
worth now, to find and hold onto purpose,

00:11:01.923 --> 00:11:05.462
to build self-respect, and to believe
that their value comes from who they

00:11:05.462 --> 00:11:07.640
are, not from what they own or achieve.

00:11:07.880 --> 00:11:11.549
Well, what's past is past; mine
has only just begun to live.

00:11:11.549 --> 00:11:15.831
But it's meant to be said in the context
of love, relationships and romance.

00:11:15.831 --> 00:11:17.360
She says mine's already past.

00:11:17.360 --> 00:11:21.030
And then, on the other hand, let
a grandmother come to confession

00:11:21.030 --> 00:11:22.865
and say, I have a friend.

00:11:25.985 --> 00:11:27.625
You see that not all have passed.

00:11:31.115 --> 00:11:35.550
It is very important that you know you
are worthy, because it is extremely

00:11:35.550 --> 00:11:39.985
important that within a relationship you
are completely free to love, so you won't

00:11:39.985 --> 00:11:45.055
have to sell yourself, nor fear anything,
and you won't wake up with a clenched jaw.

00:11:48.344 --> 00:11:54.023
Do I truly believe that I am already
loved by God, just as I am, here and now?

00:11:54.023 --> 00:11:57.178
That, indeed, is the question
you need to ask yourself.

00:11:57.178 --> 00:12:01.280
Not whether anyone else will love me,
not whether anyone else will notice

00:12:01.280 --> 00:12:05.697
me, but whether you feel deep inside
that you are truly worthy, and that

00:12:05.697 --> 00:12:09.798
God loves you exactly as you are,
regardless of whether you have someone

00:12:09.798 --> 00:12:12.322
in your life, or whether you are alone.

00:12:12.322 --> 00:12:17.055
That is the essential question: when you
are truly happy and loved, and you feel

00:12:17.055 --> 00:12:21.787
that very love coming from God, you become
ready, in that moment, to enter into

00:12:21.787 --> 00:12:23.365
a meaningful and lasting relationship.

00:12:23.885 --> 00:12:27.874
Behold this scene, which you have
heard today in the Gospel before you.

00:12:27.874 --> 00:12:31.250
You have heard today in the
Gospel that they pressed Jesus.

00:12:31.250 --> 00:12:35.853
That Jesus was making ready to slip away
from the crowd because they had heard

00:12:35.853 --> 00:12:37.388
that Jesus was performing miracles.

00:12:37.388 --> 00:12:40.763
And this crowd saw in him
nothing but a miracle worker.

00:12:40.763 --> 00:12:44.139
And then they, it is said,
began to rush at him.

00:12:44.139 --> 00:12:47.208
Literally they were already
on the verge of stoning him.

00:12:47.208 --> 00:12:52.118
And for his own safety he had to
resort to lying in order to slip away

00:12:52.118 --> 00:12:53.960
from that very crowd assembled there.

00:12:55.400 --> 00:12:59.327
How much we fling ourselves down to
the floor, again and again, please nine

00:12:59.327 --> 00:13:03.254
novenas, give the husband, give the wife,
turn this novena, turn that one, give

00:13:03.254 --> 00:13:05.778
me it like this, give me it like that.

00:13:05.778 --> 00:13:07.742
We literally bore Jesus, we crush Him.

00:13:07.742 --> 00:13:09.144
Behold, you see this crowd.

00:13:09.144 --> 00:13:11.949
Half of you came only
because the topic is love.

00:13:11.949 --> 00:13:15.596
You will not be in Lent because
the cross does not interest you.

00:13:15.596 --> 00:13:17.560
It is your hearts that interest you.

00:13:20.520 --> 00:13:23.903
And in the same way this vast
crowd pressed around Jesus.

00:13:23.903 --> 00:13:26.980
They threw themselves forward,
desperately crying out, 'give me this,

00:13:26.980 --> 00:13:29.441
give me that.' But what is the problem?

00:13:29.441 --> 00:13:32.517
What were they looking at in
Jesus, the great miracle-worker,

00:13:32.517 --> 00:13:34.055
the healer of the sick?

00:13:34.055 --> 00:13:37.747
Put differently, their own urgent,
pressing needs blinded them too, so they

00:13:37.747 --> 00:13:39.900
did not recognise Jesus as the Messiah.

00:13:39.900 --> 00:13:42.977
Look, you are here today
in this crowd as well.

00:13:42.977 --> 00:13:46.053
Have your own pressing needs
likewise blinded you from forcefully

00:13:46.053 --> 00:13:49.745
pressing your way into the church
solely because the topic is love?

00:13:50.225 --> 00:13:53.183
Are your prayers directed toward
Jesus solely and completely

00:13:53.183 --> 00:13:55.156
because of your own personal needs?

00:13:55.156 --> 00:14:00.087
Perhaps even your own needs have blinded
you before God, for you treat Him as

00:14:00.087 --> 00:14:05.348
if He were a jukebox that grants your
wish to find a husband, a wife, love,

00:14:05.348 --> 00:14:09.950
or whatever else you might be seeking—a
home, a kitten, I don’t know, really.

00:14:09.950 --> 00:14:13.567
But you understand, at times we
instrumentalise God, placing our own

00:14:13.567 --> 00:14:15.539
needs before Him, in such moments.

00:14:15.539 --> 00:14:20.142
I notice this among young people today;
some even reach the level of frustration.

00:14:20.142 --> 00:14:24.745
Well, I’m thirty; I have nobody; I
don’t feel like trying anymore, at all.

00:14:24.745 --> 00:14:28.400
She says she no longer believes
that true love exists in this life.

00:14:28.400 --> 00:14:30.930
She is deeply disappointed
in this way, I guess.

00:14:30.930 --> 00:14:34.023
And you see, we come to a
lasting blindness that arises

00:14:34.023 --> 00:14:35.429
from our own stubborn needs.

00:14:35.429 --> 00:14:39.646
We do not seek God, but we ask
God to fulfil this need for us.

00:14:39.646 --> 00:14:44.707
And so we come to despair, but if we
are aware of God's love and of our own

00:14:44.707 --> 00:14:48.925
identity that I am worth something,
and if I am alone in this life today.

00:14:49.915 --> 00:14:53.428
God, if you’ve given me someone
special, someone unlike anyone else

00:14:53.428 --> 00:14:55.345
I’ve ever met, that’s wonderful indeed.

00:14:55.345 --> 00:14:56.303
And what’s happening?

00:14:56.303 --> 00:14:57.581
Many people rush things.

00:14:57.581 --> 00:15:02.373
But when you’re aware you are loved by
God, you can wait for a relationship.

00:15:02.373 --> 00:15:04.928
You’re not in that much of a hurry.

00:15:04.928 --> 00:15:09.081
Of course it’s nice that everyone
should marry and settle down on time.

00:15:09.081 --> 00:15:12.595
But you cannot fall into crisis
and frustration just because you’re

00:15:12.595 --> 00:15:16.428
thirty now, haven’t found anyone, and
you’re tempted to rush into something.

00:15:16.428 --> 00:15:21.219
So take your time, trust in God’s plan,
and let patience light your path forward.

00:15:21.459 --> 00:15:24.342
There is nothing you can
do at this present moment.

00:15:24.342 --> 00:15:27.512
So, really, are you in any
possible way worthy of life?

00:15:27.512 --> 00:15:28.665
Yes, you are, indeed.

00:15:28.665 --> 00:15:32.988
Do you truly have any real sense of
identity if you are merely a dream?

00:15:32.988 --> 00:15:33.852
You indeed have.

00:15:33.852 --> 00:15:37.311
We simply imagined ourselves
clearly in our own minds; if I stay

00:15:37.311 --> 00:15:39.328
a dream, I am the most wretched.

00:15:39.328 --> 00:15:44.228
Of course, the Bible says it is not
good for a person to be merely a dream.

00:15:44.228 --> 00:15:48.263
But what I want to say is that,
when you are truly ready for

00:15:48.263 --> 00:15:49.704
a relationship, you can wait.

00:15:49.704 --> 00:15:54.315
Those who can't wait, who rush ahead,
would do well to look at those who have

00:15:54.315 --> 00:15:56.045
had longer relationships in life today.

00:15:56.425 --> 00:16:01.111
As soon as it ends, you can’t
even be single for a whole week.

00:16:01.111 --> 00:16:03.119
Immediately into another
serious relationship, oh—somehow

00:16:03.119 --> 00:16:04.123
something starts there.

00:16:04.123 --> 00:16:04.793
Take note.

00:16:04.793 --> 00:16:07.805
But is it luck, or is it merely flight?

00:16:07.805 --> 00:16:12.826
You all know well when you have a more
serious, truly deep love and relationship,

00:16:12.826 --> 00:16:14.834
yet we are truly emotional beings.

00:16:14.834 --> 00:16:19.186
To emotionally recover, you need
at least a full year, not a week.

00:16:19.186 --> 00:16:23.872
And I have never understood, how anyone
can be in a relationship for years,

00:16:23.872 --> 00:16:26.550
and within a week or two enter another.

00:16:27.250 --> 00:16:31.854
That means you find yourself emotionally
unhealed, and not yet wholly recovered.

00:16:31.854 --> 00:16:36.459
And you would do well to distance
yourself from emotionally unhealed people.

00:16:36.459 --> 00:16:41.447
For they can give you nothing but
pain and bitter resentment, not love.

00:16:41.447 --> 00:16:46.819
And that is precisely why I tell
you there is no cause for hurry.

00:16:46.819 --> 00:16:52.575
When you are truly aware of your own
identity and of God's love, you can

00:16:52.575 --> 00:16:54.493
make careful choices without fear.

00:16:54.493 --> 00:16:56.028
There is no despair.

00:16:56.028 --> 00:16:59.865
Secondly, you, the people around
you, are half-paralysed by fear.

00:16:59.865 --> 00:17:06.004
When you are aware of your identity and of
God's love, you can choose without fear.

00:17:07.464 --> 00:17:10.773
What's with all this fear you
seem to have about getting

00:17:10.773 --> 00:17:12.277
to know one another nowadays?

00:17:12.277 --> 00:17:16.487
And here I could really say plenty
of things about it, for us all.

00:17:16.487 --> 00:17:20.096
I strongly encourage you to meet
one another, but don't overdo it.

00:17:20.096 --> 00:17:24.608
Recently a friend of mine and I were
talking, and I said that this will

00:17:24.608 --> 00:17:29.119
end up in a sermon, because I felt
moved to say it, and perhaps many

00:17:29.119 --> 00:17:31.225
of you do the same among yourselves.

00:17:33.485 --> 00:17:37.063
While talking with one friend
the other day, I told him this

00:17:37.063 --> 00:17:41.237
would end up as a sermon, and
the topic was going out on dates.

00:17:41.237 --> 00:17:45.114
But it all started to accumulate,
mate, three or perhaps as many as

00:17:45.114 --> 00:17:46.903
four dates within a single week.

00:17:46.903 --> 00:17:50.779
And then I say, all right Sokole,
today you’ll be with one, tomorrow

00:17:50.779 --> 00:17:54.655
with another, the third day with
the third, and by Friday you won’t

00:17:54.655 --> 00:17:56.445
know which one you’ll be with.

00:17:56.445 --> 00:17:58.830
And that, in my view,
is completely natural.

00:17:58.830 --> 00:17:59.725
Why is that?

00:17:59.925 --> 00:18:02.393
So with this one, you liked the hairstyle.

00:18:02.393 --> 00:18:06.097
She is rich, she is clever, she
is serious, she is sometimes.

00:18:06.097 --> 00:18:09.491
You're confused again, you still
don't know who she'd go for.

00:18:09.491 --> 00:18:13.503
With that one you like something
about her, but it's not quite right.

00:18:13.503 --> 00:18:16.898
And now, if all that could
be brought together into one,

00:18:16.898 --> 00:18:18.750
that would be the perfect one.

00:18:18.750 --> 00:18:20.293
And what are you doing?

00:18:20.293 --> 00:18:21.219
You're confusing yourselves.

00:18:21.219 --> 00:18:22.145
You're confusing yourselves.

00:18:22.945 --> 00:18:24.358
Then, why is it that?

00:18:24.358 --> 00:18:26.620
Well, you devote yourself
to one single person.

00:18:26.620 --> 00:18:30.860
If you happen not to like it, then you
neatly and cleanly clear things up,

00:18:30.860 --> 00:18:33.122
and you set out to meet another person.

00:18:33.122 --> 00:18:36.797
And no, many people like to be
noticed, which is what I have

00:18:36.797 --> 00:18:39.624
been talking about all this time,
that something is happening.

00:18:39.624 --> 00:18:42.733
But that is not enough; it
is not a solid foundation.

00:18:42.733 --> 00:18:46.691
You know this well, and then you
cannot do it this way; I mean,

00:18:46.691 --> 00:18:48.105
you shouldn’t be doing this.

00:18:49.885 --> 00:18:55.480
And at this point there is no need for
you to be afraid if you are truly relaxed.

00:18:55.480 --> 00:18:59.521
What still paralyses so many people
is... the fear that, within any kind

00:18:59.521 --> 00:19:03.562
of relationship, in any form of bond,
they might very well lose themselves.

00:19:03.562 --> 00:19:07.292
To me, that is the most catastrophic
and devastating thing there is.

00:19:07.292 --> 00:19:10.712
How can you lose yourself if
you know yourself so well?

00:19:10.712 --> 00:19:15.374
So, only if you are insecure, we men
may, indeed, say this to one another,

00:19:15.374 --> 00:19:19.105
and even to their faces openly
refer to them as henpecked husbands.

00:19:20.125 --> 00:19:25.346
You know the man who isn’t secure
in himself; as soon as he finds some

00:19:25.346 --> 00:19:29.872
girl who’s a little sharper with her
hands, he can’t recognise him, mate.

00:19:29.872 --> 00:19:34.049
He no longer drinks, he no longer
goes out, nothing—saint of the

00:19:34.049 --> 00:19:37.878
night—and yet he doesn’t realise
that he has already lost himself.

00:19:37.878 --> 00:19:38.923
Do you understand?

00:19:38.923 --> 00:19:42.752
And many fear entering any relationship
for fear of losing themselves.

00:19:42.752 --> 00:19:44.145
And that’s understandable too.

00:19:44.145 --> 00:19:47.970
You don't need to be in any relationship
at all, not in friendship, nor in

00:19:47.970 --> 00:19:49.755
love, where you end up losing yourself.

00:19:49.755 --> 00:19:50.010
Why?

00:19:50.010 --> 00:19:51.796
Why would you have to lose yourself?

00:19:51.796 --> 00:19:56.131
Is there anyone who loves you as you are,
or would they drop you for being yourself?

00:19:56.131 --> 00:19:57.407
So don't lose yourself, people.

00:19:57.407 --> 00:19:57.662
Why?

00:19:57.662 --> 00:19:59.957
It's hard work; we're not
chameleons, or that animal.

00:19:59.957 --> 00:20:04.038
You can pretend for a month, or two in
a year, days spent in a relationship,

00:20:04.038 --> 00:20:07.098
but when you surface again—the real
you, the person you really are—then

00:20:07.098 --> 00:20:10.668
you'd better show all your worst sides
at once, so that if someone accepts

00:20:10.668 --> 00:20:12.454
you, they accept you as you are.

00:20:12.454 --> 00:20:15.769
Trying to hide your real self
behind a mask will only wear you

00:20:15.769 --> 00:20:17.300
down over time, and it hurts.

00:20:17.940 --> 00:20:21.476
Anyway, it will take him a
year or two to figure you out.

00:20:21.476 --> 00:20:22.020
Well, now.

00:20:25.274 --> 00:20:29.371
That particular sentence, the one with
which everyone here ought to move away

00:20:29.371 --> 00:20:34.097
from this place, and which carries the
sense of the whole matter, is this: that

00:20:34.097 --> 00:20:39.139
I am worthy and beloved by God, regardless
of whether I am alone, or whether I

00:20:39.139 --> 00:20:41.660
have anyone with me, or anything at all.

00:20:41.660 --> 00:20:45.756
Yet there always seems to be, somewhere
behind this sentence, the question of

00:20:45.756 --> 00:20:50.482
whether anyone loves me and whether I
am worthy of love; I must admit that

00:20:50.482 --> 00:20:52.373
there lie some wounds hidden away.

00:20:52.373 --> 00:20:56.469
That is not the kind of sentence
you utter when someone says you

00:20:56.469 --> 00:20:58.990
in such a way for no good reason.

00:20:58.990 --> 00:21:03.086
Perhaps these are not large, bleeding
wounds that are visible to all, but

00:21:03.086 --> 00:21:08.128
perhaps they are moments when we were not
noticed, or when we were not praised, or

00:21:08.128 --> 00:21:13.169
when we were not drenched in some care,
love, or empathy that may have wounded us.

00:21:13.469 --> 00:21:18.104
I say those are not the most common
wounds, the greatest ones that have

00:21:18.104 --> 00:21:20.090
killed us and are bleeding now.

00:21:20.090 --> 00:21:23.401
But all those small, very negligible
things—moments of rejection and

00:21:23.401 --> 00:21:26.380
of being overlooked, insecurities
and fears—have shaped our hearts.

00:21:26.380 --> 00:21:28.697
And that lurks somewhere deep inside us.

00:21:28.697 --> 00:21:31.015
What image of ourselves do we have?

00:21:34.905 --> 00:21:41.019
Sadly we often say and hear this,
when wounds inside us speak, we hear

00:21:41.019 --> 00:21:44.513
the line that no one will want me.

00:21:44.513 --> 00:21:48.881
If someone gets to know
me, they will leave me.

00:21:48.881 --> 00:21:54.122
It is better to have a bad
relationship than to be alone.

00:21:54.122 --> 00:21:56.743
There are also such
compromises, unfortunately.

00:21:56.743 --> 00:21:59.800
But there you must come to Jesus.

00:21:59.800 --> 00:22:02.421
Love is often a vulnerable area.

00:22:02.421 --> 00:22:08.535
And there is no one who has not
been hurt there at some time.

00:22:08.535 --> 00:22:14.213
I don't know whether that heals
or not, but the worst thing is

00:22:14.213 --> 00:22:19.455
that what happened to you in one
relationship you carry into another.

00:22:20.534 --> 00:22:24.019
Consequently, it is vitally important to
heal and become completely whole again.

00:22:24.019 --> 00:22:28.664
When Jesus heals us, he does not speak as
we do when friends console one another.

00:22:28.664 --> 00:22:32.729
Come on, you can do it; be strong,
be brave, endure this; aim for

00:22:32.729 --> 00:22:33.890
something better than this.

00:22:33.890 --> 00:22:35.632
What good is it to you?

00:22:35.632 --> 00:22:37.665
Come on, have one; this will pass.

00:22:37.665 --> 00:22:39.987
Jesus did not comfort people in that way.

00:22:39.987 --> 00:22:42.020
Jesus was the first to endure rejection.

00:22:42.020 --> 00:22:44.052
Jesus was the first to be betrayed.

00:22:44.052 --> 00:22:48.117
When Jesus hung on the cross, he
did not say, 'My God, why does

00:22:48.117 --> 00:22:50.150
this hurt me, why must I suffer?'

00:22:52.060 --> 00:22:55.283
When the pain of love comes upon
us suddenly and overwhelmingly,

00:22:55.283 --> 00:22:59.093
we are left shaken to the very
core, unable to speak or move.

00:22:59.093 --> 00:23:00.852
Why did this happen to me?

00:23:00.852 --> 00:23:02.317
What should I do now?

00:23:02.317 --> 00:23:06.127
However, Jesus does not comfort us
in the ways we commonly comfort one

00:23:06.127 --> 00:23:09.644
another; Jesus enters into our pain,
names it, and touches it deeply.

00:23:09.644 --> 00:23:11.402
And you lead us into truth.

00:23:11.402 --> 00:23:15.505
And that is the most important thing,
for this is the process by which

00:23:15.505 --> 00:23:17.264
you will gradually work through it.

00:23:17.264 --> 00:23:18.436
And what is truth?

00:23:18.436 --> 00:23:22.539
Truth is not merely a thing you
can see or hold, but a living

00:23:22.539 --> 00:23:24.004
reality that forms our lives.

00:23:24.564 --> 00:23:26.992
There has never been anyone who wanted me.

00:23:26.992 --> 00:23:28.813
Indeed, this is simply the case.

00:23:28.813 --> 00:23:31.848
Some people simply did not
know how to truly love.

00:23:31.848 --> 00:23:35.186
Observe still how these two sentences
sound very distinctly different indeed.

00:23:35.186 --> 00:23:38.828
And even when someone hurt you
very deeply, they did not know

00:23:38.828 --> 00:23:40.649
how to value your precious love.

00:23:40.649 --> 00:23:45.504
Don't say such words, don't act in that
way, never claim that no one wanted me

00:23:45.504 --> 00:23:50.360
or that I was left behind, but instead
simply say, in a calm voice, that some

00:23:50.360 --> 00:23:52.485
people didn't know how to love me.

00:23:52.825 --> 00:23:56.178
This is a very real and noticeable
difference, and, in fact, this

00:23:56.178 --> 00:23:58.134
is the very truth we should hold.

00:23:58.134 --> 00:24:02.325
Other people, at times, try to persuade
us that we are foolish, that we are

00:24:02.325 --> 00:24:05.958
worthless, that we do not know how
to value or properly appreciate love.

00:24:05.958 --> 00:24:08.193
But that is not the truth at all.

00:24:08.193 --> 00:24:12.105
The vast majority of people accept love
because they need it in their lives.

00:24:12.105 --> 00:24:14.341
However there are difficult
circumstances in life where

00:24:14.341 --> 00:24:16.017
love does not come to fruition.

00:24:16.017 --> 00:24:19.091
And please do not blame yourself;
rather, simply acknowledge that there

00:24:19.091 --> 00:24:21.606
are people who never knew how to love me.

00:24:21.606 --> 00:24:24.680
And please do not say that,
no one ever wanted me.

00:24:25.420 --> 00:24:28.873
Therefore I earnestly urge you
to heed what Jesus heard now.

00:24:28.873 --> 00:24:33.583
So that you often, in the quiet of your
heart, repeat it to yourself faithfully.

00:24:33.583 --> 00:24:38.293
And my true identity comes from God,
and God loves me exactly as I am.

00:24:38.293 --> 00:24:42.689
I am grateful to God that I am
blessed to have someone; if I

00:24:42.689 --> 00:24:47.399
currently have no one, He will send
me someone; I am in God's hands today.

00:24:47.399 --> 00:24:51.794
Do not press Jesus, and do not crush
Him, even in today's Gospel reading.

00:24:52.895 --> 00:24:53.150
Why?

00:24:53.150 --> 00:24:56.472
Because Jesus must be listened to,
and heeded with care today and always.

00:24:56.472 --> 00:24:59.795
Jesus isn't here for us, to fulfil
those desires that blind you and

00:24:59.795 --> 00:25:01.072
me today throughout our lives.

00:25:01.072 --> 00:25:04.650
I have said that many times, and I
stand by it always, truly indeed.

00:25:04.650 --> 00:25:08.228
It's good that God doesn't grant
all our desires, for not all of them

00:25:08.228 --> 00:25:10.017
are good in truth, at all times.

00:25:10.017 --> 00:25:14.362
We may be convinced at a given moment, but
not all people are right for us either.

00:25:14.362 --> 00:25:17.684
I believe you have thought this through
many times, and perhaps even about

00:25:17.684 --> 00:25:21.517
the very first love you had in life,
this and that, that and that one.

00:25:21.517 --> 00:25:24.839
And I mean it truly, with that
said, I shall carry that thought

00:25:24.839 --> 00:25:27.139
with me to the end of my life now.

00:25:27.139 --> 00:25:28.822
Well, not much at all.

00:25:28.822 --> 00:25:33.198
This happens quite often in life, but
you should not let yourself become

00:25:33.198 --> 00:25:37.237
discouraged, because until you feel
secure and strong in yourself, you will

00:25:37.237 --> 00:25:39.257
not find peace within a relationship.

00:25:39.257 --> 00:25:43.969
And that is why this sort of thing
tends to persist when two people

00:25:43.969 --> 00:25:48.008
are involved, especially if at
least one of them is immature, and

00:25:48.008 --> 00:25:50.365
even more so if both are immature.

00:25:50.365 --> 00:25:53.731
Then it turns into a kind
of general chaos indeed.

00:25:53.731 --> 00:25:57.097
It somehow keeps getting pushed
along, yet it remains always

00:25:57.097 --> 00:25:58.780
tense, and full of pressure.

00:25:59.220 --> 00:26:03.740
Just take a moment to really think
about those of you who are in

00:26:03.740 --> 00:26:05.355
relationships or who are married.

00:26:05.355 --> 00:26:08.261
Are you relaxed and feeling
comfortable in yourselves tonight?

00:26:08.261 --> 00:26:10.199
Are you without fear at all?

00:26:10.199 --> 00:26:12.459
That is love, truly pure and simple.

00:26:12.459 --> 00:26:16.657
You know, these girls in the choir
each have violins, one for each.

00:26:16.657 --> 00:26:21.500
I don't know very much about music,
but this is how I personally see it.

00:26:21.500 --> 00:26:24.407
So, sometimes our relationships are
like delicate musical instruments.

00:26:24.407 --> 00:26:28.927
You have to hit the exact level of
intensity, with just the right emphasis.

00:26:28.927 --> 00:26:32.480
If something is too quiet, you
still simply can't hear it.

00:26:33.330 --> 00:26:37.857
Yet I steadfastly believe that those
fragile strings, if you over-tighten the

00:26:37.857 --> 00:26:43.138
tiny, delicate tuning peg up there on the
headstock or even put excessive strain

00:26:43.138 --> 00:26:45.779
on the guitar itself, they will snap.

00:26:45.779 --> 00:26:48.042
A middle ground must be found.

00:26:48.042 --> 00:26:50.683
Our relationships—family, marriages,
partnerships, and friendships—have, at

00:26:50.683 --> 00:26:52.192
times, become increasingly overstrained.

00:26:52.192 --> 00:26:55.587
Just one word is enough
and the strings snap.

00:26:55.587 --> 00:26:55.965
Amen.

